<li><a href="http://www.drinkingbirds.com/" class="external text" title="http://www.drinkingbirds.com/" rel="nofollow">art project by Daniel Reynolds</a></li>
<li><a href="http://patft1.uspto.gov/netacgi/nph-Parser?Sect1=PTO1&amp;Sect2=HITOFF&amp;d=PALL&amp;p=1&amp;u=%2Fnetahtml%2FPTO%2Fsrchnum.htm&amp;r=1&amp;f=G&amp;l=50&amp;s1=2402463.PN.&amp;OS=PN/2402463&amp;RS=PN/2402463" class="external text" title="http://patft1.uspto.gov/netacgi/nph-Parser?Sect1=PTO1&amp;Sect2=HITOFF&amp;d=PALL&amp;p=1&amp;u=%2Fnetahtml%2FPTO%2Fsrchnum.htm&amp;r=1&amp;f=G&amp;l=50&amp;s1=2402463.PN.&amp;OS=PN/2402463&amp;RS=PN/2402463" rel="nofollow">Miles V. Sullivan designed the Drinking Bird in 1945 - filed for patent 2,402,463 on Aug 6, 1945</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.job-stiftung.de/index.php?id=31,143,0,0,1,0" class="external text" title="http://www.job-stiftung.de/index.php?id=31,143,0,0,1,0" rel="nofollow">Drinking Duck:</a> Demonstration experiment (instruction and video)</li>
<li><a href="http://www.annesullivanflute.com/miles/Miles_Sullivan_%20Article.pdf" class="external autonumber" title="http://www.annesullivanflute.com/miles/Miles_Sullivan_%20Article.pdf" rel="nofollow">[1]</a> Who invented the drinking bird?</li>
<li><a href="http://www.genuineideas.com/HallofInventions/SolarFerrisWheel/solarferriswheel.html" class="external text" title="http://www.genuineideas.com/HallofInventions/SolarFerrisWheel/solarferriswheel.html" rel="nofollow">a family of solar rotating toys, including a reference to a century-old ancestor of the dunking bird</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.scientificameriken.com/dbird.asp" class="external text" title="http://www.scientificameriken.com/dbird.asp" rel="nofollow">The effects of ethanol on Drinking bird</a></li>
</ul>


